            . I <rs id="t18220703-121-viclabel637" type="occupation">keep a chandler's shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220703-121-victim1055 t18220703-121-viclabel637"></join> in <placeName id="t18220703-121-crimeloc638">South Mimms</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18220703-121-crimeloc638" type="placeName" value="South Mimms"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18220703-121-crimeloc638" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220703-121-off635 t18220703-121-crimeloc638"></join>. The prisoners lodged with me from Monday till Friday. On Friday, about half-past nine o'clock, they went up stairs as if to go to bed, and twenty minutes after I found they were gone. I missed two watches and a table spoon - the watches hung up in a glass cupboard, in a room on the ground floor - I missed the shirts from a drawer. I pursued them in a cart to Barnet, and described them to the patrol - next day I found them in custody at Barnet, with all the things except one watch.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220703-121-person1057">
                  JOHN 
                  MORRISON
               <interp inst="t18220703-121-person1057" type="surname" value="MORRISON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220703-121-person1057" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220703-121-person1057" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a horse patrol. My companion gave me information - I met the three prisoners going towards town; I asked where they were going - they said to town; I secured them, and found a spoon and watch on Weston, and also two shirts; I found a handkerchief on one of them. They said they bought the watch.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
